      • menu

        public int menu()

        Menu

        Description: Displays a general menu and retrieves the user's choice. After displaying the following options, it prompts the user to enter an option and returns it.

        Options:

        1. Register a collaborator
        2. Register a department
        3. Register a request
        4. Change a request's status
          • Allows to create a Knowledge Management Project
          • Allows to create a Transformation and Improvement Project
        5. Close a project
        6. Display the last 5 projects (based on query date) of all the DTI collaborators
          • Allows to access the detailed information of a project
        7. Review efficiency:
          • DTI collaborator
          • Project
          • Request
        8. Consult general information:
          • Projects organized by priority and type
          • Projects led by every DTI team member
          • Number of received and managed requests
        9. Generate test objects
        10. Exit Program

        Preconditions:

        • The scanner object sk must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • The user's choice is returned as an integer.
        Returns:
        The user's choice.

      • registerCollaborator

        public void registerCollaborator()

        registerCollaborator

        Description: Registers a collaborator based on the user's input. This method guides the user through the process of registering a collaborator by providing options for the type of collaborator (DTI or general) and collecting relevant information such as full name, ID, email, and extension (optional). It then calls the University.registerCollaborator(int, String, String, String, String) method in the controller class to handle the registration process and returns the message indicating the success or failure of the registration.

        Preconditions:

        • intCollabType must be an int representing the type of collaboratos (1 or 2).
        • The fullName, id, email, and extension parameters must be Strings.
        • The scanner object sk must be initialized.
        • The Controller object controller must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • A collaborator is registered based on the user's input, and a message indicating the success or failure of the registration is returned.

      • registerDepartment

        public void registerDepartment()

        registerDepartment

        Description: Registers a new department in the university system. This method ensures there is at least one saved collaborator in the system before allowing department registration ((University.oneMinCollaborator()). It also checks for the existence of a department with the provided internal code before registering (University.searchDepartment(String)) Then it allows the using to enter the rest of the information. The responsable collaborator must be selected from the list made by University.displayCollaborators(). The method finally calls University.registerDepartment(String, String, String, int) to create the object.

        Preconditions:

        • internalCode must be a String.
        • name must be a String.
        • address must be a String.
        • intResponsibleCollaborator must be an int from the displayed list.

        Postconditions:

        • A new department is registered in the university system.
        • If there wasn't at least one preregistered collaborator, the system will ask the user to enter one.
        • If a department with the provided internal code already exists, an error message is displayed, and the user is prompted to try another internal code.

      • registerRequest

        public void registerRequest()

        registerRequest

        Description: Registers a new request in the system, assigning it to a responsible collaborator and department. The system will first make sure there is at least one registered collaborator (University.oneMinCollaborator()) and one department (University.oneMinDepartment()). Then it will display menus where the user can choose a preregistered collaborator (University.displayCollaborators()) and a department (University.displayDepartments()) Afterwards the use will be able to add the subject of the request and using University.isDuplicateRequest(int, String) will verify whether or not there is another request in the list inside the responsible departement. If there is no duplicate, finally, the user will enter the description.

        Preconditions:

        • controller must be initialized.
        • intResponsibleCollaborator must be an int chosen from the displayed list of collaborators.
        • intResponsibleDepartment must be an int chosen from the displayed list of departments.
        • subject must be a String.
        • description must be a String.

        Postconditions:

        • A new request is registered with the provided subject, description, responsible department, and responsible collaborator.
        • If there is not at least one collaborator registered an "at least one collaborator" message will be printed.
        • If there is not at leaste one department registered an "at least one department" message will be printed.
        • If there is another request with the same subject within the department a "duplicate" message will be printed.

      • changeRequestStatus

        public void changeRequestStatus()

        changeRequestStatus

        Description: Allows changing the status of a pending request within a department. First, it checks if there is at least one preregistered department (University.oneMinDepartment()). Second, it checks that at least one of those departments has a pending request (University.oneMinPendingRequest()). Third, it checks if there is at least one registered leader in case the pending request is accepted (University.oneMinLeader()). If either of those conditions isn't met, the appropriate message is printed. If both filters are passed, then it displays the departments that have at least one pending request (University.displayDepartmentsPendingRequest()), where the user can select one from. Then, it displays the pending requests inside this department (University.displayPendingRequests(int)) so the user can choose one. Next, the system displays the three types of status change the request to (University.displayStatusTypes()) and the user must choose one. Then, the system proceeds to change the status with University.changeRequestStatus(int, int, int). If the status is selected, then it will jump to create a project using createProject(String, String).

        Preconditions:

        • departments array must be initialized.
        • requests array must be initialized.
        • oneMinDepartment(), oneMinPendingRequest(), and oneMinLeader() methods should be in place.
        • displayDepartmentsPendingRequest(), displayPendingRequests(int), and displayStatusTypes() methods should be in place.
        • intResponsibleDepartment, intRequest, and intStatusType must all be ints within the range of the displayed menus.

        Postconditions:

        • The status of the selected pending request within the department is changed based on the provided status type.
        • If the status type is set to 2 (Approved), a project is created for the corresponding request.
        • If there is not at least one preregistered department, it will ask the user to enter one.
        • If there is not at least one pending request inside a department, the system will ask the user to enter a request.

      • createProject

        public void createProject(java.lang.String responsibleDepartment,
                          java.lang.String requestSubject)

        createProject

        Description: Creates a new project based on the approved request and user input. This method must be used after a pending request is set to approved changeRequestStatus(). This method starts by asking the type of project (knowledge or improvement) and saves the option. Then, it displays all the possible leaders (only DTI collaborators) using University.displayDtiCollaborators(). Next, displays the possible priorities a project can have (University.displayPriorities()). Afterwards, depending on the selected type of project it will ask for additional information:
        • Knowledge type: A menu displaying the possible impacted communities (University.displayImpactCommunities()) and the types of knowledge projects (University.displayKnowledgeTypes()).
        • Improvement type: The system will ask to enter the processName.
        Finally, the method invokes the methods University.createProject(String, int, int, String, String, String) to create an Improvement project or University.createProject(String, int, int, String, String, int, int) to create a Knowledge project.

        Preconditions:

        • responsibleDepartment and requestSubject must be valid strings.
        • sk must be initialized to read user input.
        • controller must be initialized to access necessary methods.
        • name and processCode must be Strings.
        • intPriority and intLeader must be integers selected from the displayed menus.

        Postconditions:

        • A Knowledge or an Improvement project is created based on the provided details.
        • The project is assigned a type, name, leader, priority, and other attributes based on user input.
        Parameters:
        responsibleDepartment - The name of the responsible department for the project.
        requestSubject - The subject of the approved request.

      • closeProject

        public void closeProject()

        closeProject

        Description: Closes a project by setting its close date. This method checks if there is at least one unclosed project (University.oneMinUnclosedProject()). If there are unclosed projects, it displays them (University.displayAllOrUnclosedOrClosedProjects(int)). The user selects one of the displayed projects, and the method prompts for the close date, ensuring it's after the registration date. The close date is parsed from user input and set for the selected project using University.closeProject(int, Calendar).

        Preconditions:

        • sk must be initialized to read user input.
        • controller must be initialized to access necessary methods.
        • intProject must be a valid integer representing the index of the project to be closed.
        • closeDateString must be a valid string representing the close date in the format dd/MM/yyyy.

        Postconditions:

        • The close date of the selected project is set based on user input.
        • A message indicating the result of the operation is returned.

      • displayProjectMatrix

        public void displayProjectMatrix()

        displayProjectMatrix

        Description: Displays the project matrix for a selected date, showing the 5 most recent projects assigned to each collaborator. The method prompts the user to enter a date, validates the date format, and retrieves project information starting from the specified date. If there are no projects (University.oneMinProject()) or no projects starting from the specified date (University.oneMinDateProject(Calendar)), appropriate messages are displayed.

        Preconditions:

        • There must be at least one registered project in the system (University.oneMinProject()).
        • The date entered by the user must be in the format dd/MM/yyyy.
        • The date entered must have projects registered from that date onwards (University.oneMinDateProject(Calendar)).

        Postconditions:

        • If the date is valid and there are projects from that date onwards, the project matrix is displayed.
        • If the date is invalid or there are no projects from that date onwards, an appropriate message is displayed.

      • accessProjectInfo

        public void accessProjectInfo(java.lang.String id,
                              java.util.Calendar date)

        accessProjectInfo

        Description: Accesses and displays detailed information of a project. After viewing the project matrix from the displayProjectMatrix() method, the user is prompted to enter a project code. If the entered code does not match any of the registered projects (University.searchProject(String)), a message indicating the nonexistence of the project is shown. The method continuously prompts the user until a valid project code is entered. It will also print the same matrix (University.displayProjectMatrix(Calendar)) for the user to double check the code. Once a valid code is provided, the detailed information of the corresponding project is displayed using the University.displayProjectInfo(String) method.

        Preconditions:

        • At least one project must be registered in the system.
        • The entered code must be a 4-letter String.
        • This method must be used after the displayProjectMatrix() method.

        Postconditions:

        • The detailed information of the selected project is displayed.
        • If the entered code does not match any of the existing projects, a message stating that the project doesn't exist is printed instead and will loop through the matrix again.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the project to access and display detailed information.
        date - The date for which the project matrix is displayed, used for presenting available project codes.

      • reviewEfficiencies

        public void reviewEfficiencies()

        reviewEfficiencies

        Description: Prompts the user to review the efficiency of a collaborator, project, or request. The method first checks if there is at least one registered leader, project, and request. If all conditions are met, it displays the available options for reviewing efficiencies and processes the user's selection. The method will then call the methods to review get the necessary info que see the efficiencies (reviewLeaderEfficiency(int), reviewProjectEfficiency(int) and reviewRequestEfficiency(int)).

        Preconditions:

        • At least one leader, project, and request must be registered in the system.
        • intEfficiency must be an int between 1 and 3.

        Postconditions:

        • If there is at least one registered leader, project, and request, the method prompts the user to select an option to review efficiencies.
        • Depending on the user's selection, it calls the corresponding method to review the efficiency of a collaborator, project, or request.
        • If the precondition is not met, it prints a message indicating the absence of registered leaders, projects, or requests.

      • reviewLeaderEfficiency

        public void reviewLeaderEfficiency(int intEfficiency)

        reviewLeaderEfficiency

        Description: Reviews and displays a leader's efficiency for a specified month. This method checks if there is at least one DTI collaborator with assigned projects(University.oneMinLeaderWProjects()). If this condition is met, it displays the list of such collaborators and prompts the user to select one(University.displayLeadersWProjects()). The user is then prompted to enter a month and year in the format "MM/yyyy" to review the efficiency for that period. The method calls the corresponding controller method to calculate and display the leader's efficiency(University.reviewLeaderEfficiency(Calendar, int)).

        Preconditions:

        • There must be at least one DTI collaborator with at least one assigned project.
        • The input date must be in the format "MM/yyyy".

        Postconditions:

        • Displays the efficiency of the selected leader for the specified month.
        • If the input format is incorrect, an error message is displayed and the method terminates.
        Parameters:
        intEfficiency - The type of efficiency to be calculated (although this parameter is not directly used in the method body, it is passed to the calculateEfficiency method).

      • reviewProjectEfficiency

        public void reviewProjectEfficiency(int intEfficiency)

        reviewProjectEfficiency

        Description: Reviews and displays the efficiency of a selected project. This method first checks if there is at least one closed project available (University.oneMinClosedProject()). If this condition is met, it displays all closed projects and prompts the user to select one (University.displayAllOrUnclosedOrClosedProjects(int)). The efficiency of the selected project is then calculated and displayed.

        Preconditions:

        • At least one project must be closed in the system.
        • intEfficiency and intProject must be ints representing a displayed option.

        Postconditions:

        • If there is at least one closed project, the efficiency of the selected project is displayed.
        • If no closed projects are available, a message indicating this is printed.
        Parameters:
        intEfficiency - The type of efficiency to be calculated (although this parameter is not directly used in the method body, it is passed to the calculateEfficiency method).

      • reviewRequestEfficiency

        public void reviewRequestEfficiency(int intEfficiency)

        reviewRequestEfficiency

        Description: Reviews and displays the efficiency of a selected request. This method first checks if there is at least one classified request available (University.oneMinClassifiedRequest()). If this condition is met, it displays all classified requests and prompts the user to select one(University.displayClassifiedRequests()). The efficiency of the selected request is then calculated and displayed.

        Preconditions:

        • At least one request must be classified in the system.
        • intEfficiency and intRequest must be ints representing a displayed option.

        Postconditions:

        • If there is at least one classified request, the efficiency of the selected request is displayed.
        • If no classified requests are available, a message indicating this is printed.
        Parameters:
        intEfficiency - The type of efficiency to be calculated (although this parameter is not directly used in the method body, it is passed to the calculateEfficiency method).

      • generalConsultations

        public void generalConsultations()

        generalConsultations

        Description: Displays a menu for general consultations and executes the selected option. This method checks if there is at least one registered leader(University.oneMinLeader()), project(University.oneMinProject()), and request (University.oneMinRequest()) in the system. If this condition is met, it presents the user with a list of available consultations. The user can select a consultation to execute, and the appropriate method is called based on the user's selection. The consultation options are:
        1. Consult the number of registered projects, ordered by type and priority (consultProjectsTypePriority()).
        2. Consult the number that each DTI collaborator has led consultLedProjects()).
        3. Consult the number of received and managed requests in a given month consultRequestsInAMonth()).

        Preconditions:

        • At least one leader, project, and request must be registered in the system.
        • intConsultation must be an int between 1 and 3.

        Postconditions:

        • If the preconditions are met, the selected consultation is executed.
        • If the preconditions are not met, an error message is displayed.

      • consultProjectsTypePriority

        public void consultProjectsTypePriority()

        consultProjectsTypePriority

        Description: Consults and displays the number of projects categorized by type and priority. This method prints a header message indicating the nature of the consultation and then calls the corresponding method (University.consultProjectsTypePriority()) from the controller to retrieve and display the required information.

        Preconditions:

        • The system must have projects registered with defined types and priorities.

        Postconditions:

        • Displays a summary of the number of projects by type and priority.

      • consultLedProjects

        public void consultLedProjects()

        consultLedProjects

        Description: Consults and displays the number of projects led by each DTI collaborator. This method prints a header message indicating the nature of the consultation and then calls the corresponding method (University.consultLedProjects()) from the controller to retrieve and display the required information.

        Preconditions:

        • The system must have registered projects and DTI collaborators assigned as leaders.

        Postconditions:

        • Displays a summary of the number of projects led by each DTI collaborator.

      • consultRequestsInAMonth

        public void consultRequestsInAMonth()

        consultRequestsInAMonth

        Description: Consults and displays the number of received and managed requests in a specified month. This method prompts the user to enter a month and year in the format "MM/yyyy" and then parses this input to create a `Calendar` object representing the first day of that month. It then calls the corresponding method (University.consultRequestsInAMonth(Calendar)) from the controller to retrieve and display the required information.

        Preconditions:

        • The input date must be in the format "MM/yyyy".

        Postconditions:

        • Displays the number of received and managed requests in the specified month.
        • If the input format is incorrect, an error message is displayed and the method terminates.

      • createBaseDtiCollaborators

        public void createBaseDtiCollaborators()

        createBaseDtiCollaborators

        Description: Initializes the system by creating four base DTI collaborators. This method delegates the creation process to the controller's University.createBaseDtiCollaborators() method.

        Preconditions:

        • The controller must be properly initialized and accessible.

        Postconditions:

        • Four base DTI collaborators are created and added to the system.

      • generateTestObjects

        public void generateTestObjects()

        generateTestObjects

        Description: Generates test objects including departments, requests, and projects. This method prints a message indicating the creation of test objects and invokes the controller's University.generateTestObjects() method to perform the actual generation.

        Preconditions:

        • The controller must be properly initialized and accessible.
        • None of the pregenerated test objects should be added.
        • The option must only be chosen once to prevent an error.

        Postconditions:

        • Test departments, requests, and projects are created and added to the system.
        • Prints a message indicating the status of the test object generation process.
